#!perl

use strict;
use warnings;

require App::Spec;
require Zing;

@ARGV=qw(help) unless @ARGV;

App::Spec->read(\Zing->data)->runner->run;

print "\n";

=encoding utf8

=head1 NAME

zing

=head1 ABSTRACT

Multi-Process Management System

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  zing - multi-process management system

  @@@@@@@   @@@  @@@@  @@  @@@@@@@@
       @@!  @@!  @@!@! @@  !@@
      !@!   !@!  !@!!@!@!  !@!
     @!!    !!@  @!@ !!@!  !@! @!@!@
    !!!     !!!  !@!  !!!  !!! !!@!!
   :!:      :!:  :!:  !:!  :!:   !::
  ::: ::::  :!:  :::   ::  :::: ::::

  Usage: zing <subcommands> [options]

  Subcommands:
  edit  Edit source spec (generate unless exists)
  init  Initialize workspace
  make  Generate source code
  spec  Generate source spec
  help  Show command help

  Options:
  --help -h         Show command help (flag)

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This tool lets you manage launch, manage, and supervise Perl 5 processes using
the L<Zing> framework from the command-line.

